qas.question: Which articles in the Norwegian Constitution allow the monarch to reject a bill that has been passed through the Sorting?
Which article in the Norweigan Constitution provides a way to override a monarch's veto?
How many elections are required to assend a bill that the monarch has vetoed?

plausible_answers.text: the monarch of Norway the right to withhold royal assent from any bill passed by the Storting
